<h2 id="section-top">Neuro-psychology services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=967">Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Floyd Unit - Birch Hill<br/>01706 754 242</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent062ef7ca293b4b52bc35dad2b26d246f">
</div>
<p>Our service is available to residents who live in the Heywood, Rochdale and Middleton (HMR) Borough or are registered with a HMR GP.</p>
<p>Floyd unit is an 18 bedded unit; the age group accepted is from 18 years onwards both male and female. We provide a dedicated multidisciplinary team who offer 24 hour care and therapy support to patients.</p>
<p>Our service provides and delivers a therapeutic rehabilitation plan to all patients by meeting individual needs, goals, and abilities, to enable them to lead as independent life as is possible.</p>
<p>Who will patients meet while under your department’s/service’s care?</p>
<p>The team is multidisciplinary to include care staff, doctor, Admin, Pharmacy Team, Occupational therapist Team, Physiotherapist team &amp; Social workerers.</p>
<p>When is the service available?</p>
<p>The inpatient unit is open 24 hours a day , 365 days a year.</p>
<p>Where is the service provided?</p>
<p>The Floyd Unit , Birch Hill Hospital , Birch Road , Rochdale,  OL12 9QB</p>
<p>Department contact details</p>
<p>The Floyd unit 01706 754 242</p>
<p>The Floyd Unit  is managed by the Pennine Acute Hospitals Trust</p>
<p>Key staff/consultants</p>
<p><strong>Unit Manager Rosemary Law</strong></p>
<p><strong>Clinical Lead Dr Fayez Morcos</strong></p>
<p>Lead Nurse (Louisa Harkness-Hudson)</p>
<p>Assistant Director of Nursing (Jackie Heatley)</p>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
